  <Docs>
    <summary>Identifies the color primaries of a color space using CICP (Coding-Independent Code Points) as defined by ITU-T H.273.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKColorspacePrimariesCicp` specifies the color primary chromaticities and white point of a color space using the standardized numeric codes defined in ITU-T H.273 (Coding-Independent Code Points). These values are used with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorSpace.CreateCicp*> to create a color space from a CICP primaries and transfer function pair.

## Examples

```csharp
var cs = SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(
    SKColorspacePrimariesCicp.Rec709,
    SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp.Rec709);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
